Governor Godwin Obaseki of Edo State on Sunday mourned the passing of Pastor Temitope Balogun Joshua, AKA T.B Joshua, the General Overseer of the Synagogue Church of All Nations (SCOAN) Obaseki in a statement in Benin on Sunday expressed shock over the sudden demise of Prophet Joshua and explained that the man of God impacted the lives of millions of people across the world. He said the cleric deployed his gift of delivering the word of God in relatable terms to advance the Church of Christ and brought laughter, solace and comfort to many with Christ’s message of love. He said the Synagogue Church of All Nations was a home of refuge for those desirous of God’s word and also for the desolate, providing a beacon of hope to many worshippers from across the globe. The Governor said the prophet would be remembered for his devotion to God, the feisty manner he delivered Christ’s message of love and his commitment to community and the upliftment of mankind. He commiserated with the Christian community, the Church, the prophet’s family and prayed that God grants all the fortitude to bear the irreparable loss. SCOAN Church confirms TB Joshua’s death, last words 